description:
The HRule control creates a single horizontal line. You typically use this control to create a dividing line within a container.  <p>The HRule control has the following default properties:</p> <table class=&quot;innertable&quot;> <tr> <th>Characteristic</th> <th>Description</th> </tr> <tr> <td>Default size</td> <td>The default width is 100 pixels, default height is 2 pixels. By default, the HRule control is not resizable; set width and height to percentage values to enable resizing.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>strokeWidth</td> <td>2 pixels.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>strokeColor</td> <td>0xC4CCCC.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>shadowColor</td> <td>0xEEEEEE.</td> </tr> </table>   <p>The <code>&lt;mx:HRule&gt;</code> tag inherits all of the tag attributes of its superclass, and adds the following tag attributes:</p>  <pre>
 &lt;mx:HRule
 <strong>Styles</strong>
 strokeColor=&quot;0xC4CCCC&quot;
 shadowColor=&quot;0xEEEEEE&quot;
 strokeWidth=&quot;2&quot;
 /&gt;
 </pre>
